The White House has issued a statement condemning the sentencing of Meriam Yahya Ibrahim Ishag in Sudan. She was sentenced to be flogged for adultery and hanged to death for apostasy because she married a Christian man. The statement calls on the Government of Sudan to meet its obligations under international human rights law and respect Ms. Ishag's right to freedom of religion. Sudan has been designated as a Country of Particular Concern for its ongoing violations of religious freedom. The statement urges Sudan to fulfill its promise of religious freedom and respect the universal human rights of its people.